.TH PODCTL 1 "2026" "podctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
podctl \- control AirPods from the Linux terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B podctl
.RI [ options ]
.I command
.RI [ args ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B podctl
is a command-line frontend for AirPods on Linux. It talks to the local
audio stack (PipeWire/PulseAudio via
.BR pactl (1))
and to Bluetooth (BlueZ via
.BR bluetoothctl (1)),
and uses the Apple Accessory Protocol over an L2CAP channel for
features the AirPods firmware exposes directly (listening modes,
conversation awareness, button mappings, battery telemetry).
.PP
.B podctl
runs daemon-first: when
.BR podctld (1)
is reachable on the per-user Unix socket
.IR $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/podctl.sock
it routes through the daemon for instant, fresh responses. Otherwise it
falls back to a standalone mode that handles audio and Bluetooth
operations directly; AAP-only operations require the daemon and surface
a clear error.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Device state
.TP
.B status
Full snapshot: model, battery, mode, settings, audio, bluetooth.
.TP
.B battery, b, bat
Battery levels for left bud, right bud and case.
.SS Listening modes
.TP
.BI "mode " "off|anc|transparency|adaptive"
Switch listening mode. Adaptive requires AirPods Pro 2 or AirPods 4 ANC.
.TP
.BI "conv " "on|off"
Conversation awareness (Pro 2 / AirPods 4 ANC only).
.TP
.BI "spatial " "off|fixed|head-tracked"
Spatial audio mode.
.SS Bud settings
.TP
.BI "ear " "on|off"
In-ear auto-pause detection.
.TP
.BI "mic " "auto|left|right"
Microphone selection.
.TP
.BI "loud-reduction " "on|off"
Cap loud sound spikes (Apple's hearing-safety feature). The AAP setting
ID for this is not yet pinned down; the verb currently returns
"not implemented" on every device.
.TP
.BI "press " "left|right " "mode-cycle|siri|none"
Stem press-and-hold action. Same status as
.B loud-reduction
above \(em verb is wired, AAP write is not.
.TP
.BI "tone " "on|off"
Acoustic feedback on press. Same status as
.B loud-reduction
above.
.TP
.BI "rename " """name"""
Change the Bluetooth name.
.TP
.BI "one-bud-anc " "on|off"
Keep ANC active when only one bud is being worn (Pro 2).
.TP
.BI "auto-anc " "0..100"
AutoANC / Adaptive Audio strength (Pro 2).
.TP
.BI "chime " "0..100"
System tone / chime volume.
.SS Bluetooth
.TP
.B connect, disconnect
Bring the link up or down.
.TP
.B pair, unpair
Pair or forget the AirPods.
.TP
.B list, ls
List paired AirPods on this adapter.
.TP
.BI "auto-connect " "on|off"
BlueZ trusted/auto-connect flag.
.SS Audio
.TP
.BI "volume " "0..100"
Set output volume on the AirPods sink.
.TP
.BI "mute " "on|off"
Mute or unmute the AirPods sink.
.TP
.BI "profile " "high|headset|off"
Bluetooth audio profile: high-fidelity A2DP, HSP/HFP headset, or off.
.TP
.BI "codec " "sbc|aac|aptx|ldac|..."
Switch A2DP codec (availability depends on PipeWire build).
.TP
.B default
Make the AirPods the system's default audio sink.
.TP
.BI "latency " "<ms>"
Output latency offset; negative values delay audio.
.SS Streaming
.TP
.B watch, w
Live event stream until interrupt: connection, battery, in-ear, mode,
button presses.
.TP
.BR "meter" " [" "--plain" "|" "--json" "] [" "--once" "] [" "--interval " N "] [" "--device " name ]
Live RMS and peak dBFS of the audio currently routed to the AirPods.
Software meter \(em measures the digital signal, not eardrum SPL.
Requires
.BR parec (1)
from
.IR pulseaudio-utils .
.SS Misc
.TP
.B ping
Daemon health check.
.TP
.BI "completion " "bash|zsh|fish"
Emit shell completion script to standard output.
.TP
.BI "help " [ command ]
Top-level help or detailed help for one verb.
.TP
.B version, --version, -V
Print version and daemon status.
.SS System
.TP
.BR "debug " [ --no-redact ]
Paste-friendly diagnostic report. Redacts identifying data unless
.B --no-redact
is given.
.TP
.BI "debug emit-case-lid " "open|close"
Emits a synthetic case-lid event for testing the popup. Requires the
daemon.
.TP
.BI "tray " "start|stop|status|restart"
Manage the
.B podctl-tray
status-bar icon (systemd user service). Connection and battery show in
the tooltip. Left-click shows the popup by default; right-click opens
the menu. The left-click action is configurable in
.IR ~/.config/podctl/tray.toml
.RB ( "left_click = popup|mode-cycle|toggle-anc-tr|menu" ).
.TP
.B popup
Ask the running
.B podctl-popup
to show the bubble now (model, connection, battery, mode) \(em the same
bubble shown on case-open, mode change, or connect.
.TP
.B reboot
Restart the installed systemd user services
.RB ( podctld ", " podctl-tray ", " podctl-popup ).
No root required; units that are not installed are skipped.
.TP
.BR "install " [ --yes "] [" --no-daemon "] [" --no-completion "] [" --no-manpages "] [" --with-tray "] [" --with-popup ]
Install binaries, completion, man pages and systemd user services to
.IR ~/.local .
No root required.
.TP
.BR "uninstall " [ --yes ]
Remove everything
.B install
put in place. Idempotent.
.IP
If the running binary lives in a system bin dir (i.e. it was installed
via the AUR
.B podctl-bin
or
.B podctl-git
package), this verb delegates to
.B sudo pacman -R <pkg>
instead and stops the user services first. Use
.B --yes
to skip the prompt; the sudo password prompt still appears.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Emit responses as JSON instead of human-readable text. Useful in scripts.
.TP
.B --help, -h
Print help (top-level or, after a verb, the verb's detailed page).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Daemon socket lives at
.IB $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR /podctl.sock\fR.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
User configuration directory; the
.B no-daemon
opt-out marker lives at
.IB $XDG_CONFIG_HOME /podctl/no-daemon\fR.
.TP
.B NO_BANNER
When set, suppress the "running without daemon" banner.
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Sets daemon log level (default
.IR info ).
Example:
.BR "RUST_LOG=debug podctld" .
.SH EXIT STATUS
Follows BSD
.BR sysexits.h :
.B 0
on success,
.B 64
for a usage error,
.B 65
for malformed data,
.B 69
when a required service is unavailable,
.B 70
for an internal software error,
.B 71
for an OS error.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/podctl.sock
Daemon control socket (mode 0600, owner-only).
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/podctl/
User configuration directory.
.TP
.I ~/.config/systemd/user/podctld.service
systemd user service unit (recommended).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR podctld (1),
.BR bluetoothctl (1),
.BR pactl (1),
.BR wpctl (1),
.BR systemctl (1).
.SH BUGS
Report at the project's issue tracker on GitHub. The Apple Accessory
Protocol is reverse-engineered; some byte layouts are best-effort and
may differ between AirPods firmware revisions.
